        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_7849.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">John Power</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">The signatories included the headmasters of the major boys’ schools and other educational establishments, as well as well-known public figures.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">The Previous Examination, colloquially known as the ‘Little-Go’, was a test of Latin, ancient Greek, mathematics, and theology for all second-year undergraduates at <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_795.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Cambridge University</ref> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_8441.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Winstanley 1947</ref>, pp. 144–5). In 1868, CD had been concerned that <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1226.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Horace Darwin</ref>, who intended to study for a science degree, might not pass the Little-Go as he was ‘backward’ in classics (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 16, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5962.xml">letter to R. C. M. Rouse, [after 12 March 1868]).</ref></note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">In March 1879, the Senate of the University of Cambridge appointed a committee to consider this memorial and the questions arising from it, but the request to remove Greek from the examination was rejected in 1880 (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_8441.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Winstanley 1947</ref>, pp. 178–80). </note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_683.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Henry Austin Bruce</ref>, Baron Aberdare.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f6"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4688.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Frederick Temple</ref>, bishop of Exeter.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f7"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_8421.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Richard Monckton Milnes</ref>, Baron Houghton.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f8"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_9066.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">John Laird Mair Lawrence</ref>, Baron Lawrence.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f9"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_8315.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">James Fraser</ref>, bishop of Manchester.</note>
        </div>
        
    
        
